  "name": "Greek Lemon-Garlic Sirloin with Roasted Broccoli and Tzatziki",
  "description": "Seared sirloin with oregano and lemon, served alongside roasted garlic broccoli and a cool tzatziki drizzle. Mild, quick, and keto-friendly.",
  "servings": "Serves 4",
  "prep_steps": [
    "Preheat oven to 220°C/425°F.",
    "Cut broccoli into florets; dry well.",
    "Mince garlic.",
    "Zest and halve the lemon.",
    "Pat dry beef sirloin steak and season both sides with salt and black pepper.",
    "Set tzatziki out at room temperature."
  ],
  "cook_steps": [
    "On a sheet pan, toss broccoli with 2 tbsp olive oil, half the minced garlic, half the lemon zest, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Roast broccoli for 15–18 minutes, turning once, until edges are browned and tender.",
    "While broccoli roasts, heat 1 tbsp olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear beef sirloin steak 3–4 minutes per side for medium-rare (thickness dependent).",
    "Reduce heat to low; add butter, remaining garlic, oregano, and remaining lemon zest to the pan. Spoon over steak for 30–60 seconds.",
    "Transfer steak to a board to rest 5 minutes.",
    "Squeeze half the lemon over roasted broccoli and toss.",
    "Slice steak against the grain. Serve with tzatziki and remaining lemon wedges."
  ],
